The test is failing because `userRepository.save(...)` is called **twice**, not once:

1. First inside `synchronize(...)`, after creating/updating the user.
2. Again inside `synchronizeNewUserWithPing(...)`, when Ping fails and the user is saved with:

```java
pingSyncStatus = "FAILED"
pingLastError = ...
```

Your verification currently expects exactly one call:

```java
verify(userRepository)
        .save(any(UserEntity.class));
```

Change it to:

```java
verify(userRepository, times(2))
        .save(any(UserEntity.class));
```

Add:

```java
import static org.mockito.Mockito.times;
```

A stronger test is to capture both saves and verify the final state:

```java
@Test
void shouldMarkPingSynchronizationAsFailedAndRethrow() {
    service = createService(true);

    RuntimeException pingException =
            new RuntimeException("Ping unavailable");

    when(userRepository.findByGpsGroupNumber("testuser"))
            .thenReturn(Optional.empty());

    when(salesPointRepository.findBySalesPointId("POS-001"))
            .thenReturn(Optional.empty());

    when(relationshipRepository
            .findByPersonUserIdAndSalesPointIdAndRelationshipType(
                    anyString(),
                    anyString(),
                    anyString()
            ))
            .thenReturn(Optional.empty());

    doThrow(pingException)
            .when(pingUserClient)
            .createUser(any(UserEntity.class));

    RuntimeException result = assertThrows(
            RuntimeException.class,
            () -> service.synchronize(request)
    );

    assertSame(pingException, result);

    ArgumentCaptor<UserEntity> captor =
            ArgumentCaptor.forClass(UserEntity.class);

    verify(userRepository, times(2))
            .save(captor.capture());

    UserEntity finalSavedUser =
            captor.getAllValues()
                    .get(captor.getAllValues().size() - 1);

    assertEquals(
            "FAILED",
            finalSavedUser.getPingSyncStatus()
    );

    assertEquals(
            "Ping unavailable",
            finalSavedUser.getPingLastError()
    );

    verify(pingUserClient)
            .createUser(any(UserEntity.class));
}
```

Imports:

```java
import org.mockito.ArgumentCaptor;

import static org.mockito.Mockito.doThrow;
import static org.mockito.Mockito.times;
```

One important Mockito detail: because your mock likely uses:

```java
when(userRepository.save(any(UserEntity.class)))
        .thenAnswer(invocation -> invocation.getArgument(0));
```

both captured entries may point to the same mutable `UserEntity` instance. So checking the last captured value is correct, but comparing the first and second states may not work reliably because the same object was modified between calls.
